ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 1
 shows the XRD pattern of Cu2O/GQDs composite prepared in the different solvents (ethanol (sample 10), water (sample 3), and acetone (sample 9)). As seen from the XRD patterns, Cu2O/GQDs composites were successfully prepared in the different solvents. XRD pattern of Cu2O shows the good agreement with (JCPDS#73–0687). It crystalized in cubic phase with following miller index: (110), (111), (200) and (211). Sharp peaks in Fig. 1 a shows that Cu2O/GQDs composite shows the higher crystallinity when ethanol was used as the solvent. In addition, amorphous like background could be observed which is related to the GQDs. We used Energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDX) as more evidence for the synthesis of Cu2O/GQDs composites (Fig. 2
). EDX of sample 1–6 is presented in Fig. 2a–f. The EDX results approve the presence of carbon element related to GQDs and Cu and O element related to the Cu2O in Cu2O/GQDs composites.
